The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Indian boxers advance

New Delhi: All four Indian pugilists moved into the second round in the 13th World Boxing Championship in Mianyang City, China. 

Som Bahadur Pun overcame the challenge of Kevin Bizier of Canada to win 26-24 in the opening round in the lightwelter division on Monday. 

In the bantamweight category, Commonwealth champion Akhil Kumar defeated Serdar Avei of Turkey 28-15 while Vijender Kumar defeated Lithuanias Darius Jasevicius 31-17 in the welterweight class on Sunday. 

Suranjay Singh entered the second round untested as he got a bye in the opening round of the lightfly division. 

